On 10 Nov 2010, at 4:45, Yaron Minsky wrote:
> let ( |! ) x f =3D f x
This is the same as F#'s pipe operator (|>) which I find extremely =
useful because with it code reads the way it works, not backwards:
2 |> tenfold |> add 1 |> double  =3D> 42
(ok, this is a ridiculous example, but you get the point).
